   "source": [
    "# Binary Trees: Terminology & Traversals \u2014 Practice \u2014 \u26a0\ufe0f SOLVED / ANSWER KEY \u26a0\ufe0f\n",
    "\n",
    "**\u26a0\ufe0f This is the SOLVED / answer-key version, for instructor use or post-deadline release only. Do not distribute before students have completed the exercise.**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Instructions:** for each Part, **fill in and run every exercise block first**, then run the **checker cell** at the end of that Part to grade all of them at once. Don't run the checker cell partway through \u2014 any exercise you haven't filled in yet will simply be marked wrong, since it still holds its empty default value.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Format:** every question gives you a place to type a plaintext answer (a word, short phrase, or a comma-separated sequence) directly into a `String` variable. **Running an exercise cell only saves your answer \u2014 it does not grade it.** Grading happens in the separate checker cell further down (one checker per Part, covering several exercises at once). You can edit your answers and re-run both the exercise cells and the checker cell as many times as you like.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Time budget:** roughly 60 minutes total.\n",
    "- Part 1 \u2014 Terminology (~15 min)\n",
    "- Part 2 \u2014 Traversal definitions (~10 min)\n",
    "- Part 3 \u2014 Hand-tracing traversals on given trees (~35 min)\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the setup cell below first \u2014 it only needs to run once."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8e82fc30",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "// Checks a single short-answer term against a list of acceptable answers.\n",
    "// Comparison is case-insensitive and ignores leading/trailing whitespace.\n",
    "public boolean checkTerm(String given, String... accepted) {\n",
    "    String norm = given.trim().toLowerCase();\n",
    "    for (String a : accepted) {\n",
    "        if (norm.equals(a.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n",
    "            System.out.println(\"Correct!\");\n",
    "            return true;\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    System.out.println(\"Not quite. You answered: \\\"\" + given + \"\\\"\");\n",
    "    return false;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "// Checks a traversal sequence like \"X, Q, M, T, R, Z, J\" against the correct sequence.\n",
    "// Accepts variation in spacing/commas and is case-insensitive.\n",
    "public boolean checkSequence(String given, String correctCsv) {\n",
    "    String[] givenParts = given.trim().toLowerCase().split(\"[,\\\\s]+\");\n",
    "    String[] correctParts = correctCsv.trim().toLowerCase().split(\"[,\\\\s]+\");\n",
    "    boolean ok = Arrays.equals(givenParts, correctParts);\n",
    "    if (ok) {\n",
    "        System.out.println(\"Correct! Sequence: \" + String.join(\", \", correctParts));\n",
    "    } else {\n",
    "        System.out.println(\"Not quite.\");\n",
    "        System.out.println(\"  You answered:  \" + String.join(\", \", givenParts));\n",
    "        System.out.println(\"  Correct order: \" + String.join(\", \", correctParts));\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    return ok;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "System.out.println(\"Checker functions loaded.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9c1c7125",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
