    "---\n",
    "## Part 3 \u2014 Hand-Tracing Traversals (~35 min)\n",
    "\n",
    "For each tree below, work out each traversal **by hand** (no code, no running anything except the checker) and type the sequence of node labels as a comma-separated list, e.g. `X, Q, M, T, R, Z, J`. Spacing doesn't matter and the checker is case-insensitive.\n",
    "\n",
    "In addition to preorder/inorder/postorder, each tree also asks for a **level-order** traversal: visit nodes level by level (the \"Level 1, Level 2, ...\" levels from Part 1's terminology), and within each level, visit left to right.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Each tree's diagram is repeated above every question so you don't have to scroll back and forth. Fill in all of a tree's exercises first, then run that tree's checker cell.**"
   ]
  },
