    "\n",
    "**3j (BONUS).** Tree 1 and Tree 2 do **not** produce alphabetically-ordered inorder traversals, even though their node labels are still just letters. What property does a tree need to have for inorder traversal to always come out in sorted order? You don't need to write code \u2014 describe it in your own words.\n",
    "\n",
    "*Hint: think about how each node's value compares to everything in its left branch versus everything in its right branch \u2014 and whether that has to be true just at the root, or at every node in the tree.*\n",
